text: This is a list of Oman Twenty20 International cricketers. ==Team history== The team's debut came in its last match of the tournament, the fifth-place play- off against Afghanistan.International Twenty20 matches played by Oman – CricketArchive. Retrieved 17 November 2015. Oman lost the match, played at Castle Avenue, Dublin, by five wickets.(25 July 2015). "All-round Afghanistan finish fifth with easy win" – ESPNcricinfo. Retrieved 17 November 2015. ==Team status== Oman maintained their T20I status until 2019. In April 2018, the ICC granted full Twenty20 International (T20I) status to all its members, starting from 1 January 2019. Therefore, Oman will retain its T20I status. ==Key== General * – Captain * – Wicket-keeper * First – Year of debut * Last – Year of latest game * Mat – Number of matches played Batting * Runs – Runs scored in career * HS – Highest score * Avg – Runs scored per dismissal * 50s – Number of half centuries * * – Batsman remained not out Bowling * Wkt – Wickets taken in career * BBI – Best bowling in an innings * Ave – Average runs per wicket Fielding * Ca – Catches taken * St – Stumpings affected ==List of players== Last updated 24 February 2022Players / Oman / T20I caps – ESPNcricinfo.
